  <div class="paragraph">
  <h2 id="myparagraph"><p>Hi! My name is Cole and I've been a fan of horror and supernatural fiction podcasts since 2016; I was very intimidated by horror media when I was younger, but I've found that podcasts strike the perfect balance between fascinating and disturbing. I mostly enjoy serialized podcasts where a larger, over-arching story is told through weekly episodes, but I can appreciate anthological, vignette podcasts as well.</p><p>I have a fairly low tolerance for poor acting or sub-par audio design, so unless otherwise noted, you can be assured that my recommendations here avoid that for the most part. </p><p>Outside of podcasts, I enjoy lots of different video games, mostly rpgs or story-driven indie games, as well as cooking, playing with my cat, and kpop. </p></h2>
